commit.message: Sync test files with the Math-BigInt distribution

Implement _lucas() in XS

- Implement _lucas() in XS code.

- Don't test _lucas() in list context. The _lucas() method in
  Math::BigInt::GMP always returns just a single value.

Implement _fib() in XS

- Implement _fib() in XS code.

- Don't test _fib() in list context. The _fib() method in
  Math::BigInt::GMP always returns just a single value.

Implement _nok() in XS

- Implement _nok() in XS code.

- Skip some of the largest test cases, since mpz_bin_ui(), which does
  the main work in _nok(), can't handle values larger than the maximum
  unsigned integer.

- Fix some errors in the test for _nok(). Some values were duplicated
  and others were missing.

Version 1.6013

- Sync test files with the Math-BigInt distribution.

- Remove obsolete link to cpanratings.org.

Version 1.6011

- Sync test files with Math-BigInt.

Version 1.6010

- Update documentation.

- Make t/01load.t display the output from gmp_version().

- Update required version of modules in Makefile.PL.

Merge pull request #4 from FGasper/gmp_version

Add static gmp_version() function.

commit.message:
Version 1.6009

- Sync test files with Math-BigInt.

Remove shebang from Makefile.PL

On Cygwin, depending on the configuration of Cygwin, a file will be
considered executable if it has a shebang, and if Makefile.PL is an
executable file, it is considered a "Kwalitee Issue".

Version 1.6008

- Sync test files with Math-BigInt.

- Update documentation.
